    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chambers encased in thick, fireproof vaults of clay, brick, or stone; particularly suited for baking bread.  The bake oven was sometimes built in a separate structure, outside the living quarters of the home; some bake ovens were communal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
